    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. A function called `turn_right(this_painter)` is already written for you in `custom.py`. It turns the `Painter` to the right using three `turn_left()` commands.\r\n\r\n2. In `main.py`, import the `turn_right()` function from the `custom` module at the top of your file so you can use the function.\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   from custom import turn_right\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n3. Save `custom.py` to your **Backpack** so you can reuse the `turn_right()` function later!\r\n\r\n   :::details [**How do I save files to my Backpack?**]\r\n   ![](https://images.code.org/5d21b631aa68d348a70dec9024a8f086-image-1744817649137.png)\r\n   :::\r\n\r\n4. Use `turn_right(painter_name)` to turn your `Painter` and help them paint in front of the traffic cones. For example:\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   mila = Painter()\r\n   mila.move()\r\n   turn_right(mila)\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n \r\n![](https://images.code.org/145189e2adad132757591a501534cff6-choiceC.gif)",
